snippet.title: Faith in the Future  (The Economy Will Rise) (Barron Trump Singing Imagined)
snippet.description:
Faith in the Future  (The Economy Will Rise)

Check us out on Spotify! https://open.spotify.com/album/3y1CZVxPBVqYl2ljdNVWno?si=lLRWLYbeQcuXD9TQDeKi7A

⬇️⬇️⬇️ Watch more videos below! ⬇️⬇️⬇️
https://youtu.be/WBHJZs8ZeFQ
https://youtu.be/GAdihLnAiXk
https://youtu.be/SZZW8YMZlMg?si=kP7ZE5s5fhhjjpX2
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hq_JjAodbY0

Lyrics:
Verse 1
Prices up, shelves are thin,
Feels like the world’s wearing thin.
But I’ve seen storms and brighter skies,
With prayer and faith, we will rise.

Pre-Chorus
It’s not just numbers, stocks, or gold,
It’s hearts that trust, and hands that hold.
When we call on God, He hears our cry,
Lifts our burdens, lifts us high.

Chorus
The economy will rise through prayer,
With hope in hearts and love to share.
God provides, He always will,
Even when the world stands still.
So let us pray, both near and far,
He heals the land, He knows who we are.

Verse 2
Jobs may fade, but dreams don’t die,
With every tear, He’s standing by.
Faith’s not found in dollar signs,
But in the peace that God designs.

Pre-Chorus
It’s not just headlines, graphs, or fear,
It’s trusting Him year after year.
Through every crash, through every climb,
He moves in love, He moves in time.

Chorus
The economy will rise through prayer,
With hope in hearts and love to share.
God provides, He always will,
Even when the world stands still.
So let us pray, both near and far,
He heals the land, He knows who we are.

Bridge
Bow your head, lift your voice,
In troubled times, faith is our choice.
Miracles come when hearts align,
And God says, “This nation is still mine.”

Chorus
The economy will rise through prayer,
With hope in hearts and love to share.
God provides, He always will,
Even when the world stands still.
So let us pray, both near and far,
He heals the land, He knows who we are.

Outro
So don’t lose hope, don’t lose grace,
He’s still moving in this place.
Through every valley, every care,
We’ll rise again—through faith and prayer.
